<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="617" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363 Barco/80: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Piles</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-17T13:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 17,
                                        1928—1 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>13. Report briefly by cable present status of Barco case and endeavor to
                            expedite decision promised within a month, as reported in your 11,
                            February 17, 4 p.m.<note n="9" xml:id="d617fn9">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>